2.description:
This map shows the number of US Americans with ancestry from various European countries according to self-reported 2019 American Community Survey data.

10 numbers shown on the map:
1. 34,000,000 - England/UK
2. 45,000,000 - Germany
3. 3,400,000 - Sweden
4. 1,200,000 - Denmark
5. 8,000,000 - France
6. 16,000,000 - Italy
7. 9,000,000 - Poland
8. 1,100,000 - Ukraine
9. 1,300,000 - Spain
10. 54,000 - Iceland

According to this map, Germany has the highest number of US Americans with ancestry at 45,000,000, followed closely by the United Kingdom (England) at 34,000,000. These two countries represent the largest sources of European ancestry for Americans based on this self-reported data.
